  "prompt": "Which organ is supplied with most blood.?",
  "response": "The organ that receives the most blood flow is the liver. The liver receives approximately 25-30% of the body's cardiac output. It is supplied predominantly by the hepatic artery and the portal vein. The hepatic artery provides oxygenated blood, while the portal vein delivers nutrient-rich blood from the intestines. This extensive blood supply is vital for the liver's numerous functions, including detoxification, metabolism, and production of vital proteins.",
